result.execSummary:
Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt:
01:27 PM Defendant Aubrey Keven Pinager appeared by video means.  Attorney Brian J. Juech appeared by video means for Plaintiff State of Wisconsin. Attorney Mark J Gumz appeared by video means for Defendant Aubrey Keven Pinager.
21CM113, 22CM5 & 21TR1147 tracking together:
Atty Gumz states that the matter is resolved.    Court questions the defendant regarding in-person appearance.  Defendant waives their in-person appearance today & will proceed by zoom.

  Atty Juech states plea agreement to Count 1 in 21CM113.  22CM5 to be dismissed and read-in.  Atty Gumz agrees and states that this would be a time served sentence.  Atty Juech agrees.  Defendant agrees.

  Court questions defendant regarding plea. Advises of Constitutional Rights and elements of the charge.  Defendant enters a No Contest plea.  
Court finds plea made knowingly, voluntarily & Intelligently.  Court relies on the criminal complaint for a factual basis.  

BY THE COURT:  Court finds a sufficient factual basis to support the charges.  Court accepts defendant's plea and finds defendant guilty of Count 1 in 21CM113 and orders the judgment of conviction as of today's date.   22CM5 to be dismissed and read-in. 21TR1147 to be dismissed

Atty Gumz makes sentencing arguments.
Defendant makes a statement to the court.

BY THE COURT:  21CM113:  Court orders 10 days in the Marquette County Jail; consecutive to any other sentence
Credit = 8
Good Time
Time Served
Court Costs = $243.00
Submit DNA sample within 60 days if not done so already and pay surcharge = $200.00
  Defendant agrees to the $15.00 payment plan fee.
Payment Plan:  $50.00/month commencing on May 1, 2022

22CM5 to be dismissed and read-in.
21TR1147 to be dismissed

02:20 PM Defendant Aubrey Keven Pinager appeared by video means. Prosecuting Atty Clifford C. Burdon appeared for State of Wisconsin. Attorney Mark J Gumz in court for Defendant Aubrey Keven Pinager.
22CM5 & 21CM113 tracking together:
Atty Gumz states that he has discovery and did speak with his client; requests another reset.

BY THE COURT:  Set another status
  Status hearing scheduled for April 4, 2022 at 01:30 pm.
